Localisation::cUserLocalisedString.English: 6C58 10:45 Heathfield-St Blazey S.S

Morning driver! Please prepare the cab, then shunt forward to "Heathfield South Reverse" where we'll add some CDA's to the rear of the train. Our loco is on test following a heavy exam at Laira and should be driven cautiously where possible.
Change the points and set back onto the rake of CDA wagons.
Remember that your maximum permitted speed on this working is 60mph!
We'll need to stop at Newton Abbot briefly to drop off a member of the crew.
Right away if you have the road. We'll be stopping at Tavistock Yard to collect some more wagons.
Make sure you stop fully clear of the points at Tavistock Junction so we can reverse onto the Up Line to access the yard.
Set back to Tavistock Up Main Reverse. Make sure the road is set in the map as there's no signal!

Now pull forward to Tavistock Reversal West, set the points if they aren't already set! We're not due to depart the yard until 12:25 so there's no real rush to do our shunting. We're going to be collecting that rake of VCA's in the headshunt
Set the points for Tavistock Siding and leave your train as far back as possible without fouling the through road, which we'll need to use to collect the vans.
Pull forward to Tavistock Reversal West
Set back along the through road and collect the rake of vans from Tavistock Yard East Headshunt.
Pull forward to Tavistock Reversal West, make sure you fully clear the points at the entrance to the yard.
Set back and collect the rest of our train from Tavistock Siding
Pull forward to the far end of Tavistock Reversal West so that we can then set back onto the Up Main at departure time (12:15).
Set the points up to the main line and then wait until P199, or if it's already cleared you may reverse onto the Up Line to await our booked time of 12:27.
Depart for Plymouth when you have the road, this will be after 1V36 passes at 12:25.
Good work driver. Now continue to Par on Cornish Main Line (Extension).
